<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=865&amp;p=57562#p57562"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Google search shows that the Famicom microphone is a level detector that connects to bit D2 of controller 1. This bit exists only on the expansion port of a front-loader, not the controller ports on the front panel. See also <a href="http://www.nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=31913" class="postlink">previous Famicom mic discussion</a>.<br /></div><br /><br />So either I'll have to run a separate line to the expansion port from the joypad itself, or from the expansion port to the data line on the controller port within the NES. Either one is easily doable. <br /><br />Thanks!<br /><br />-Xious<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4070">Xious</a> — Fri Mar 05, 2010 9:22 am</p><hr />
