<title type="html"><![CDATA[Famicom controller II MIC]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=865&amp;p=57558#p57558"><![CDATA[
Google search shows that the Famicom microphone is a level detector that connects to bit D2 of controller 1. This bit exists only on the expansion port of a front-loader, not the controller ports on the front panel. See also <a href="http://www.nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=31913" class="postlink">previous Famicom mic discussion</a>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Mar 05, 2010 9:08 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
